I won't be able to have mokkori any more.

25
00:02:05,525 --> 00:02:10,485
Ryo is the Love Thief!
Hidden Love Affair Behind the Magic Mirror
(Part 2)

26
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:17,403
Ryo, wake up! How long do you
need to sleep?

27
00:02:17,403 --> 00:02:19,939
No way, I'm tired.

28
00:02:19,939 --> 00:02:21,741
I'm going to pass on the training today.

29
00:02:21,741 --> 00:02:23,710
It would be impossible to train today,
even if you wanted to,

30
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:26,577
because Kasumi is gone. Hey, wake up!

31
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:35,313
No, I can't let him get involved.

32
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:40,192
I don't want to make Mr. Saeba suffer
because of my selfishness.

33
00:02:42,228 --> 00:02:44,219
Everything will be solved if I give up.

34
00:02:53,873 --> 00:02:56,342
You're now telling me you'll marry me,

35
00:02:56,342 --> 00:02:59,038
therefore you want me to release him
from the hypnotic state.

36
00:03:00,513 --> 00:03:01,810
Yes.

37
00:03:03,616 --> 00:03:06,019
You love Saeba that much, I guess.

38
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:10,456
I thought he was just a tool to cancel
the engagement with me.

39
00:03:11,157 --> 00:03:13,259
It's none of your business.

40
00:03:13,259 --> 00:03:14,726
What's your answer?

41
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,597
Sure.

42
00:03:17,597 --> 00:03:18,898
Really?

43
00:03:18,898 --> 00:03:20,763
But in order to prove what you said,

44
00:03:25,672 --> 00:03:28,539
why don't we do it right now
as husband and wife?

45
00:03:40,019 --> 00:03:41,486
Who did this?!

46
00:03:42,188 --> 00:03:44,088
You should be grateful that it wasn't a knife.


47
00:03:44,524 --> 00:03:48,119
If it was, your snobby nose
would have been gone.

48
00:03:48,528 --> 00:03:50,496
Jerk, when did you get here?!

49
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:52,022
Mr. Saeba!

50
00:03:55,768 --> 00:03:57,203
Let's go home.

51
00:03:57,203 --> 00:03:58,504
But I...

52
00:03:58,504 --> 00:04:02,668
I only have one day left for the
special training, teacher.

53
00:04:03,843 --> 00:04:05,310
Mr. Saeba...

54
00:04:06,279 --> 00:04:09,510
Wait! Jerk, you can't leave!

55
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:13,214
It will be tomorrow before I see you again.

56
00:04:13,586 --> 00:04:15,053
Bye.

57
00:04:19,492 --> 00:04:21,323
Why are you still going to do this?

58
00:04:21,794 --> 00:04:25,423
If I give up, you'll be able to
get your power back.

59
00:04:25,865 --> 00:04:27,457
It's a simple plan, isn't it?

60
00:04:29,235 --> 00:04:34,240
I'm sure you really thought you were right,
and the rule was stupid.

61
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:38,506
I can't believe that you're
giving up that easily.

62
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:40,212
Oh, no.

63
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:41,848
But...

64
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:43,440
Then, believe me.

65
00:04:43,816 --> 00:04:46,686
Once I accept a request from
a client, I complete it.

66
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:48,916
That's the pride of being a professional.

67
00:04:49,422 --> 00:04:50,889
Mr. Saeba!

68
00:04:56,095 --> 00:04:58,264
Takashi is a master of hypnosis,

69
00:04:58,264 --> 00:05:00,867
but his physical abilities are nothing special.

70
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:03,062
I know you won't lose, if you can be yourself.

71
00:05:03,503 --> 00:05:05,835
But I feel he's not the same as usual.

72
00:05:06,939 --> 00:05:10,272
Well, it might be because he doesn't
have his wild mokkori power.

73
00:05:10,677 --> 00:05:12,269
Do you think he has a chance to win?

74
00:05:15,081 --> 00:05:16,708
We have to do something.

75
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:30,363
Hi, how are you, Grandma?

76
00:05:30,363 --> 00:05:31,731
You're late.

77
00:05:31,731 --> 00:05:34,734
The other leaders and I were
about to give up on you.

78
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:36,369
I see.

79
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:39,439
These old men are judges, aren't they?

80
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:41,737
And you are the leader of
the judges, aren't you?

81
00:05:43,042 --> 00:05:46,307
I thought you ran away because
you got scared.

82
00:05:46,746 --> 00:05:50,307
Now, leaders, would you please
start explaining the game?

83
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,283
The target you need to steal tonight is...

84
00:06:03,329 --> 00:06:04,831
This.

85
00:06:04,831 --> 00:06:10,269
There's a mirror just like this one
where a mirror craftsman lives.

86
00:06:10,269 --> 00:06:13,573
Whichever one can steal it faster, wins.

87
00:06:13,573 --> 00:06:15,174
That's it?

88
00:06:15,174 --> 00:06:17,039
That's what it's all about?

89
00:06:18,644 --> 00:06:21,772
It's too easy for the final test.

90
00:06:22,248 --> 00:06:24,216
But, Grandma...

91
00:06:41,968 --> 00:06:43,435
The mirror...

92
00:06:44,003 --> 00:06:46,072
A reflection on the ceiling?

93
00:06:46,072 --> 00:06:47,673
Mr. Saeba, what are you looking at?

94
00:06:47,673 --> 00:06:49,208
Nothing.

95
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:51,676
This is the mirror. Look at it very carefully.

96
00:06:59,485 --> 00:07:01,387
Now, time to start.

97
00:07:01,387 --> 00:07:03,122
Wait a second, Grandma.

98
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:05,658
I don't see Kasumi. Where is she?

99
00:07:05,658 --> 00:07:09,185
You really don't know how to speak
properly to your elders, do you?

100
00:07:14,534 --> 00:07:15,268
Kasumi?

101
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:18,571
Wow, it's been a while since I've seen
you in that mokkori leotard.

102
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:21,474
What's the matter with you,
in an outfit like that?

103
00:07:21,474 --> 00:07:23,533
Grandma, I have a favor to ask.

104
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,546
Mr. Saeba is an amateur.

105
00:07:26,546 --> 00:07:28,247
Please give him a handicap.

106
00:07:28,247 --> 00:07:31,083
As his handicap, please
let me be his support.

107
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:32,448
What?

108
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,053
No.

109
00:07:34,053 --> 00:07:35,655
But...

110
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:37,390
I don't care.

111
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:40,293
A handicap is necessary.

112
00:07:40,293 --> 00:07:43,963
I was thinking that this game would be no fun
for me because he's an amateur.

113
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:48,434
When they understand they can't win
even with both of them trying,

114
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:50,994
Kasumi will marry me without
saying anything.

115
00:07:51,370 --> 00:07:54,771
Okay, if you say so.

116
00:07:55,575 --> 00:07:57,907
I give you permission to be his support.

117
00:07:59,946 --> 00:08:01,914
I didn't expect you to hate me that much.

118
00:08:02,748 --> 00:08:06,650
I'm so happy just thinking that
you'll be mine soon.

119
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:12,917
Ready? Start!

120
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:32,345
Kasumi, I kind of understand
how you feel, but...

121
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:33,937
The rule is the rule.

122
00:08:37,383 --> 00:08:39,476
Follow me closely, Mr. Saeba.

123
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:43,723
Wow, I'm so happy.

124
00:08:43,723 --> 00:08:46,325
The Flying Tush is still fine.

125
00:08:46,325 --> 00:08:48,461
My cute tush!

126
00:08:48,461 --> 00:08:49,894
How embarrassing!

127
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:56,669
I see, since he doesn't have
any mokkori power,

128
00:08:56,669 --> 00:08:59,572
she needs to guide him like that
or he can't do anything.

129
00:08:59,572 --> 00:09:03,064
However, from my point of view,
it's more complicated than that.

130
00:09:07,146 --> 00:09:09,580
I can't believe they gave me
a sketch of the house.

131
00:09:11,317 --> 00:09:13,649
This is too easy.

132
00:09:22,728 --> 00:09:25,464
Please accept my thanks for spreading
rumors about me all over town.

133
00:09:25,464 --> 00:09:27,193
Now you learn, snob!

134
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:31,037
You jerk, Saeba!

135
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:34,006
How dare you damage such a
beautiful face as mine?!

136
00:09:35,274 --> 00:09:37,176
However, no matter how you struggle,

137
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:39,278
the winner is already decided, and it's me.

138
00:09:39,278 --> 00:09:42,475
May you live your entire life
without any mokkori!

139
00:09:43,516 --> 00:09:47,043
Anyway, about this test,
my feelings are mixed.

140
00:09:47,353 --> 00:09:48,820
What do you mean?

141
00:09:49,288 --> 00:09:53,759
Our family is prohibited from stealing
something for ourselves.

142
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:57,129
When we receive a request, we judge
whether the request is fair or not.

143
00:09:57,129 --> 00:09:59,393
If it's fair, we take back something
which had been stolen before.

144
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:04,070
However, Grandma is making us steal
something without a good reason.

145
00:10:04,070 --> 00:10:05,230
It's the first time.

146
00:10:06,205 --> 00:10:10,301
Kasumi, who is Yayoi Asou?

147
00:10:10,977 --> 00:10:13,846
It's Grandma's name,

148
00:10:13,846 --> 00:10:16,337
but how do you know that?

149
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,508
Well, not a big deal.

150
00:10:40,339 --> 00:10:43,399
If the sketch is correct, it
should be in this room.

151
00:10:45,544 --> 00:10:47,011
