00:16:42,334 --> 00:16:43,460
What?!

247
00:16:44,136 --> 00:16:48,374
I think this mirror was made by
lovers who had to separate.

248
00:16:48,374 --> 00:16:53,379
They instilled it with their hope to meet
again, and they each kept one.

249
00:16:53,379 --> 00:16:57,076
This mirror might be worth more
than their life to the owner.

250
00:16:57,950 --> 00:17:02,978
We shouldn't take something like this
regardless of the situation.

251
00:17:03,722 --> 00:17:06,625
Mr. Saeba, you didn't steal this

252
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:08,217
because you found out the meaning
of this mirror, didn't you?

253
00:17:08,961 --> 00:17:11,897
Then, the purpose of this test
might have been to find out

254
00:17:11,897 --> 00:17:15,134
how much the person understands the
meaning of our family business.

255
00:17:15,134 --> 00:17:18,103
It sounds old-fashioned, but I guess so.
Right, Grandma?

256
00:17:19,905 --> 00:17:22,141
You are so conceited, aren't you, Takashi?

257
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:24,871
You forgot the pride and the heart
of our family, didn't you?

258
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:27,913
You are neither qualified to
be Kasumi's husband,

259
00:17:27,913 --> 00:17:30,649
nor to take our family name.

260
00:17:30,649 --> 00:17:32,344
Go away right now!

261
00:17:37,356 --> 00:17:39,756
No way...

262
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:42,027
I'm impressed, Saeba.

263
00:17:42,027 --> 00:17:44,463
You understand our family so well.

264
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:48,300
